"'''First Contact'''" is a short story written by [[Timothy Zahn]] with illustrations by [[Mike Vilardi]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 1|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 1]] in [[February]] [[1994]] and later reprinted in ''[[The Best of the Star Wars Adventure Journal, Issues 1-4]]'', both by [[West End Games]]. It was subsequently featured in the short story anthology ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'' published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[November]] [[1997]] before being made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]. Supplementary game information was provided by [[Peter M. Schweighofer]]. 

The story takes place in [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]].

==Plot summary==
[[Smuggler/Legends|Smuggler]] [[Talon Karrde]] and his [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]] [[Quelev Tapper]] travel to [[Varonat/Legends|Varonat]] to investigate private [[Morodin/Legends|Morodin]]-[[Hunting/Legends|hunting]] [[Gamgalon's Morodin-hunting safari|safaris]] held by [[Gamgalon]], a [[Krish (species)/Legends|Krish]]. Karrde suspects that Gamgalon is up to something worth knowing about. Karrde fakes [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] problems in order to stay on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] long enough to take part in a safari. Before leaving on the safari, Karrde meets the [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] [[Technician/Legends|mechanic]] working on his [[Starship/Legends|ship]], Celina Marniss. Karrde immediately senses that there is more to her than meets the eye.

On the safari, Karrde and Tapper discover that Morodin are a sentient and peaceful [[Species/Legends|species]] that are butchered during these safaris. Before they can escape, Karrde and Tapper are caught by Gamgalon and his crew. Gamgalon reveals that [[Aleudrupe berry/Legends|aleudrupe berries]] grown in soil rich with Morodin [[Slime/Legends|slime]] have specific chemical properties that allow them to serve as a catalyst in a synthesized [[Blaster gas/Legends|blaster gas]]. The safaris are a mask for the planting and harvesting of the [[Yagaran aleudrupe plant]]s.

Tapper attempts to fight his way out of the Krish trap, but is killed. Karrde survives when the hyperdrive mechanic, Celina Marniss, arrives in the jungle and kills all of the Krish. In return for saving Karrde's life, Marniss wants only one thing, a job. Karrde agrees and Marniss reveals her true name: [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]].

==Continuity==
This short story related the first meeting of [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] and [[Talon Karrde]]. Mara's alias of Celina Marniss, was a nod to a former coworker in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's court]], as revealed in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' ([[1996]]). In ''[[X-Wing: The Bacta War]]'' ([[1997]]), Talon Karrde employed [[Melina Carniss]], but in ''First Contact'', set after that novel, he showed no recognition of what would therefore be an obvious pseudonym used by Mara.<ref name="TERC" />

